{
  "texts": [
    "Both the training loss and validation loss were compared after 70 epochs of MAE pre-training, to get an early indication of performance without wasting too many resources on optimization.",
    "Based on the grid search outcomes, initially a W learning rate of 3.0 × 10 -4 was chosen for BP and 1.0 × 10 -3 for DBP, together with a R learning rate of 2.5 × 10 -4, as these yielded the lowest training loss values after 70 epochs.",
    "However, observing the training curves and later performance revealed that for BP, a W learning rate of 5.0 × 10 -4 yielded slightly better performance and more stable training.",
    "Observing the validation loss after 70 epochs for DBP reveals that a R learning rate of 5.0 × 10 -4 gives a better generalization performance, so we chose that for the R learning rate instead.",
    "Figure 7 shows the grid search outcomes."
  ]
}